(43, 21, 20, 43, 21, 7, 7, 'the disciple whom Jesus loved', 'Discipleship and Recognition of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the role of ''the disciple whom Jesus loved'' in recognizing Jesus. In John 21:7, this disciple identifies Jesus to Peter, while in John 21:20, Peter sees this disciple following Jesus. This connection highlights the importance of this disciple in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
