(43, 21, 20, 43, 21, 24, 24, 'disciple whom Jesus loved', 'Connection of the Beloved Disciple', 'This connection highlights the identity of the disciple whom Jesus loved, linking Peter''s inquiry about betrayal to the testimony of this disciple. Both passages emphasize the significance of the beloved disciple''s role in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
